ued%20a%20case%20in%201998%20with%20several%20states.%20The%20central%20claim%20of%20the%20landmark%20case%20was%20that%20Microsoft%20created%20a%20monopoly%20through%20its%20operating%20systems%2C%20choking%20competitors%20like%20Netscape%20and%20Apple.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20first%20decision%20in%20what%20became%20a%20winding%20Microsoft%20lawsuit%20would%20have%20broken%20up%20the%20company%20into%20two%2C%20one%20for%20the%20operating%20system%20and%20the%20other%20for%20software%20production.%20Appeals%20ended%20in%20a%202001%20settlement%20that%2C%20among%20other%20measures%2C%20required%20Microsoft%20to%20share%20parts%20of%20its%20source%20code%20with%20third%20parties.%20Such%20sharing%20was%20meant%20to%20catalyze%20more%20development%20%E2%80%94%20though%20some%20states%20thought%20that%20solution%20was%20inadequate.%20But%20the%20company%20was%20not%20split%20up%20and%20it%20remains%20a%20tech%20juggernaut.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20Thursday%2C%20the%20DOJ%20argued%20that%20the%202001%20Microsoft%20settlement%20let%20Apple%20build%20its%20tools%20on%20Windows%20products%2C%20like%20iTunes%20for%20Windows%20personal%20computers.%20On%20the%20heels%20of%20that%20success%2C%20Apple%20kept%20innovating%20and%20struck%20gold%20with%20the%20iPhone%20and%20its%20App%20Store%20to%20become%20an%20entrenched%20tech%20player%20well%20beyond%20desktop%20computers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENow%2C%20the%20DOJ%20and%2016%20attorneys%20general%20are%20going%20after%20Apple%2C%20employing%20similar%20arguments%20that%20they%20used%20against%20Microsoft.%20Prosecutors%20said%20Apple%20has%20its%20hands%20in%20too%20many%20pots%20and%20suppresses%20competition%20for%20everything%20from%20payments%20to%20smart%20watches%20by%20%26quot%3Bdelaying%2C%20degrading%2C%20or%20outright%20blocking%26quot%3B%20other%20technology.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EApple%20plans%20to%20fight%20the%20lawsuit%2C%20which%20it%20said%20in%20a%20statement%20would%20%26quot%3Bset%20a%20dangerous%20precedent%2C%20empowering%20government%20to%20take%20a%20heavy%20hand%20in%20designing%20people's%20technology.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20government%20hasn't%20won%20a%20big%20tech%20antitrust%20case%20like%20Microsoft%20since%2C%20although%20it's%20trying%20a%20similar%20playbook%20with%20Google's%20parent%20company%20Alphabet.%20That%20trial%20wrapped%20up%20in%20November%20and%20is%20awaiting%20the%20judge's%20decision%3B%20he%20said%20at%20closing%20arguments%20that%20he%20had%20%26quot%3Bno%20idea%26quot%3B%20how%20he%20would%20rule.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMicrosoft%20appeared%2026%20times%20in%20Thursday's%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.justice.gov%2Fopa%2Fmedia%2F1344546%2Fdl%3Finline%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecomplaint%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20most%20by%20far%20of%20any%20tech%20company.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmicrosoft-1990s-antitrust-case-looms-over-apple-2024-3%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1711095641000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65fd3f352417f97b87ce4d7e%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmicrosoft-1990s-antitrust-case-looms-over-apple-2024-3%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%202001%20settlement%20already%20figures%20prominently%20in%20the%20case%20against%20Apple.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22insider%40insider.com%20(Meghan%20Morris)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A32%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmicrosoft-1990s-antitrust-case-looms-over-apple-2024-3%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22'2023%20Was%20Hottest%20Year%20on%20Record%2C%202024%20to%20Get%20Worse'%3A%20WMO%20Report%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2021%2F08%2F17121156%2Fheat-wave.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20The%20year%20that%20passed%20was%20not%20just%20hot.%20It%20was%20the%20hottest%20by%20far%20than%20any%20year%20ever%20recorded%20and%20broke%20several%20major%20global%20climate%20records%2C%20confirms%20yet%20another%20report%3A%20the%20World%20Meteorological%20Organisation%E2%80%99s%20(WMO%E2%80%99s)%20annual%20State%20of%20the%20Global%20Climate%20report%20released%20on%20March%2019.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAnd%20the%20year%20we%E2%80%99ve%20entered%20may%20not%20hold%20much%20respite%20either%3A%202024%20is%20likely%20to%20get%20worse%2C%20the%20report%20has%20warned.%20With%20increasing%20greenhouse%20gas%20levels%2C%20global%20and%20sea%20surface%20temperatures%2C%20sea%20levels%2C%20and%20depleting%20Antarctic%20and%20Arctic%20sea%20ice%20cover%20and%20glacier%20retreats%20also%20breaking%20records%20in%202023%2C%20the%20UN%20body%20has%20issued%20a%20%E2%80%9CRed%20Alert%E2%80%9D%20to%20the%20world.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20good%20news%20is%20that%20renewable%20energy%20generation%20has%20been%20surging.%20Funding%20to%20tackle%20and%20adapt%20to%20climate%20change%20is%20also%20higher%20now%20than%20it%20was%20before%20%E2%80%93%20but%20it%E2%80%99s%20still%20not%20enough.%20However%2C%20not%20acting%20would%20be%20far%20worse%2C%20with%20damages%20mounting%20to%20USD%201%2C266%20trillion%20between%202025%20and%202100%20alone%2C%20according%20to%20the%20WMO%20report.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20report%20comes%20just%20in%20time%20to%20inform%20discussions%20at%20the%20crucial%20Copenhagen%20Climate%20Ministerial%20which%20kicked%20off%20in%20Denmark%E2%80%99s%20Copenhagen%20on%20(March%2021).%20The%20Ministerial%20is%20the%20first%20official%20meeting%20after%20the%20last%20Conference%20of%20Parties%20(COP28)%3B%20here%2C%20climate%20leaders%20and%20ministers%20from%20around%2040%20countries%20will%20discuss%20the%20outcomes%20of%20COP28%20and%20the%20expectations%20for%20the%20upcoming%20COP29%20at%20Baku%2C%20Azerbaijan.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EOn%20March%2021%2C%20the%20UN%20Development%20Programme%20(UNDP)%20also%20launched%20the%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.undp.org%2Flibya%2Fpress-releases%2Fun-development-programme-disrupts-global-television-airwaves-shocking-weather-forecasts-future-mobilize-climate-action-today%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CWeather%20Kids%20campaign%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20%E2%80%93%C2%A0%20created%20in%20partnership%20with%20WMO%20and%20The%20Weather%20Channel%20%E2%80%93%20in%20which%20children%2C%20dressed%20up%20as%20meteorologists%2C%20call%20for%20urgent%20climate%20action%20for%20their%20future.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3E2023%2C%20a%20year%20that%20shattered%20heat%20records%C2%A0%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ELast%20year%20shattered%20several%20heat%20records%3A%20in%20India%2C%20across%20Asia%20and%20the%20world.%20February%202023%20was%20the%20hottest%20on%20record%20in%20India%20since%201901%2C%20the%20India%20Meteorological%20Department%20(IMD)%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fenvironment%2Findia-heatwave-conditions-imd%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Eannounced%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E.%20And%20it%20would%20get%20hotter%2C%20the%20IMD%20predicted.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIt%20was%20right.%20India%20reeled%20under%20a%20severe%20heat%20wave%20in%20April%202023.%20On%20May%2017%2C%20climate%20scientists%20part%20of%20the%20World%20Weather%20Attribution%20group%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fenvironment%2Fclimate-change-april-2023-heat-wave-india%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Efound%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20that%20human-induced%20climate%20change%20made%20the%20April%20heat%20wave%20across%20India%20and%20Bangladesh%2030%20times%20more%20likely.%20The%20June%20that%20followed%20was%20the%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fenvironment%2Fjuly-3-world-hottest-day%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Ehottest%20June%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20that%20south%20peninsular%20India%20had%20ever%20witnessed.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EJuly%20broke%20more%20records.%20July%203%20was%20the%20world%E2%80%99s%20hottest%20day%20ever%20recorded%2C%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fenvironment%2Fjuly-3-world-hottest-day%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Erevealed%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20climate%20data%20from%20the%20US%20National%20Centers%20for%20Environmental%20Prediction.%20Around%20mid%20July%2C%20NASA%E2%80%99s%20top%20scientists%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fenvironment%2Fnasa-warns-july-2023-likely-to-be-warmest-month-on-record%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Etold%20reporters%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20that%20the%20month%20was%20likely%20to%20be%20the%20warmest%20month%20on%20record%20in%20%E2%80%9Chundreds%2C%20if%20not%20thousands%2C%20of%20years%E2%80%9D%2C%20and%20that%20the%20heat%20would%20only%20get%20worse.%20The%20first%20three%20weeks%20of%20July%20were%20the%20warmest%20three-week%20period%20ever%20recorded%2C%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fenvironment%2Fjuly-2023-the-hottest-ever-month-on-record-likely-warmest-in-tens-of-thousands-of-years%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Eas%20per%20a%20report%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20released%20by%20the%20World%20Meteorological%20Organisation%20on%20July%2027.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20October%202023%2C%20the%20European%20Union%E2%80%99s%20Copernicus%20Climate%20Change%20Service%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fenvironment%2F2023-on-track-to-become-hottest%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Ereported%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20that%20the%20year%20was%20set%20to%20become%20the%20hottest%20year%20ever%20recorded%2C%20with%20September%20being%20the%20warmest%20ever%20on%20record.%20The%20Service%20also%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fclimate.copernicus.eu%2Fcopernicus-2023-hottest-year-record%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Enoted%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20that%20December%202023%20was%20the%20warmest%20December%20on%20record%20globally.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ESeveral%20agencies%20and%20organizations%20released%20reports%20and%20statements%20in%20January%20confirming%20that%202023%20was%20a%20year%20that%20broke%20heat%20records.%20The%20IMD%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.deccanherald.com%2Findia%2Fimd-says-2023-was-second-warmest-year-for-india-since-1901-2831841%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Esaid%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20in%20January%20this%20year%20that%202023%20was%20the%20second%20warmest%20year%20for%20India%20since%201901.%20The%20Copernicus%20Climate%20Change%20Service%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fclimate.copernicus.eu%2Fcopernicus-2023-hottest-year-record%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Econfirmed%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20that%202023%20was%20the%20warmest%20calendar%20year%20in%20global%20temperature%20data%20records%20dating%20back%20to%201850.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EHottest%20year%20in%20174%20years%20of%20record-keeping%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWMO%2C%20a%20body%20under%20the%20UN%2C%20has%20also%20confirmed%20that%202023%20was%20the%20hottest%20year%20to%20be%20recorded%20ever%20since%20climate%20records%20began%20in%201850.%20In%20its%20annual%20State%20of%20the%20Climate%20report%20released%20on%20March%2019%2C%20the%20WMO%20noted%20that%20the%20shift%20from%20La%20Ni%C3%B1a%20to%20El%20Ni%C3%B1o%20conditions%20in%20mid-2023%20contributed%20to%20the%20rapid%20rise%20in%20temperature%20from%202022%20to%202023.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CDecreased%20monsoon%20rainfall%20in%20southeast%20Asia%20is%20associated%20with%20El%20Ni%C3%B1o%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20report%20said.%20%E2%80%9COnset%20of%20the%20monsoon%20over%20Kerala%2C%20India%2C%20occurred%20on%208%20June%2C%207%20days%20later%20than%20normal.%20By%20the%20end%20of%20September%2C%20India%20had%20received%2094%25%20of%20its%20typical%20monsoon%20rainfall%E2%80%A6Higher%20than%20normal%20rainfall%20totals%2C%20however%2C%20were%20observed%20along%20the%20lower%20course%20of%20the%20Indus%20River%20and%20in%20central%20India.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThese%20are%20some%20of%20the%20major%20take%20homes%20of%20the%20report%2C%20ranging%20from%20heat%20records%20the%20world%20broke%20in%202023%2C%20and%20other%20impacts%20that%20the%20year%20witnessed%20due%20to%20human-induced%20climate%20change%3A%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cul%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20global%20mean%20near-surface%20temperature%20in%202023%20was%201.45%20%C2%B1%200.12%20%C2%B0C%20above%20the%20pre-industrial%201850-1900%20average.%20That%E2%80%99s%20higher%20than%20the%20last%20hottest%20years%20(2016%2C%20at%201.29%20%C2%B1%200.12%20%C2%B0C%3B%20and%202020%20at%201.27%C2%B10.13%20%C2%B0C).%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20last%20nine%20years%20%E2%80%93%20from%202015%20to%202023%20%E2%80%93%20were%20the%20nine%20warmest%20years%20on%20record.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3E%3Cspan%3EWidespread%20marine%20heatwaves%20raised%20global%20average%20sea-surface%20temperatures%2C%20which%20were%20at%20a%20record%20high%20from%20April%20onwards%2C%20with%20records%20in%20July%2C%20August%20and%20September%20broken%20by%20a%20huge%20margin.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20global%20mean%20sea%20level%20reached%20a%20record%20high%20as%20per%20satellite%20records%20(since%201993)%2C%20reflecting%20continued%20ocean%20warming%2C%20and%20the%20melting%20of%20glaciers%20and%20ice%20sheets.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3E%3Cspan%3ESatellite%20data%20showed%20that%20Antarctic%20sea-ice%20extent%20reached%20a%20record%20low%20(since%201979)%20in%20February%202023%20and%20remained%20at%20a%20record%20low%20for%20June%20till%20early%20November.%20Arctic%20sea%20ice%20too%20remained%20well%20below%20normal.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3E%3Cspan%3ESeveral%20glaciers%20retreated%20to%20a%20historic%20low%3A%20the%20global%20set%20of%20reference%20glaciers%20(a%20collection%20of%20about%2040%20glaciers%20across%20the%20world%20which%20are%20studied%20to%20understand%20both%20the%20accumulation%20and%20loss%20of%20ice)%20for%20the%20hydrological%20year%202022-2023%20experienced%20the%20largest%20loss%20of%20ice%20ever%20since%20records%20began%20in%201950.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20observed%20concentrations%20of%20three%20main%20greenhouse%20gases%20%E2%80%93%20carbon%20dioxide%2C%20methane%2C%20and%20nitrous%20oxide%20%E2%80%93%20reached%20record%20levels%20in%202022.%20These%20continued%20to%20increase%20in%202023.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3E%3Cspan%3EWeather%20and%20climate%20extremes%2C%20along%20with%20other%20factors%2C%20have%20doubled%20the%20number%20of%20people%20who%20are%20facing%20acute%20food%20insecurity%20across%20the%20world%3A%20from%20149%20million%20people%20before%20the%20COVID-19%20pandemic%2C%20to%20333%20million%20people%20in%202023%20(in%2078%20monitored%20countries%20by%20the%20World%20Food%20Programme).%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ful%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EA%20%E2%80%98Red%20Alert%E2%80%99%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EExtreme%20weather%20events%20%E2%80%93%20heat%20waves%2C%20wildfires%2C%20droughts%2C%20floods%2C%20cyclones%20%E2%80%93%20were%20many%2C%20and%20impacted%20people%20and%20communities%20across%20the%20world%2C%20the%20report%20highlighted.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CNever%20have%20we%20been%20so%20close%20%E2%80%93%20albeit%20on%20a%20temporary%20basis%20at%20the%20moment%20%E2%80%93%20to%20the%201.5%C2%B0%20C%20lower%20limit%20of%20the%20Paris%20Agreement%20on%20climate%20change%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20WMO%20Secretary-General%20Celeste%20Saulo%2C%20in%20a%20press%20release.%20%E2%80%9CThe%20WMO%20community%20is%20sounding%20the%20Red%20Alert%20to%20the%20world.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CClimate%20change%20is%20about%20much%20more%20than%20temperatures.%20What%20we%20witnessed%20in%202023%2C%20especially%20with%20the%20unprecedented%20ocean%20warmth%2C%20glacier%20retreat%20and%20Antarctic%20sea%20ice%20loss%2C%20is%20cause%20for%20particular%20concern%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20said.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EHowever%2C%20there%20is%20one%20silver%20lining.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ERenewable%20energy%20generation%20is%20surging.%20In%202023%2C%20renewable%20capacity%20additions%20increased%20by%20almost%2050%25%20from%202022%20for%20a%20total%20of%20510%20gigawatts%20(GW)%2C%20the%20report%20noted.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CSuch%20growth%20marks%20the%20highest%20rate%20observed%20in%20the%20past%20two%20decades%20and%2C%20as%20the%20International%20Energy%20Agency%20(IEA)%20indicates%2C%20demonstrates%20the%20potential%20to%20achieve%20the%20clean%20energy%20goal%20set%20at%20COP28%20to%20triple%20renewable%20energy%20capacity%20globally%20to%20reach%2011%2C000%20GW%20by%202030%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20report%20said.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%202021-2022%2C%20global%20climate-related%20finance%20flows%20%E2%80%93%20funding%20for%20adapting%20to%20and%20mitigating%20climate%20change%20%E2%80%93%20also%20increased.%20It%20reached%20almost%20USD%201.3%20trillion%2C%20nearly%20double%20when%20compared%20to%202019-2020%20levels%2C%20the%20report%20noted.%20However%2C%20it%E2%80%99s%20still%20not%20enough.%20According%20to%20the%20report%2C%20%E2%80%9Cannual%20climate%20finance%20investments%20need%20to%20grow%20by%20more%20than%20six%20times%2C%20reaching%20almost%20USD%209%20trillion%20by%202030%20and%20a%20further%20USD%2010%20trillion%20through%20to%202050%E2%80%9D.%20Funding%20for%20adaptation%20strategies%2C%20particularly%2C%20is%20lagging%20behind.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EBut%20that%20doesn%E2%80%99t%20mean%20we%20shouldn%E2%80%99t%20act.%20The%20cost%20of%20inaction%20is%20far%20higher%2C%20despite%20the%20large%20financing%20gap%2C%20the%20report%20said.%20Between%202025%20and%202100%2C%20the%20report%20estimates%20that%20the%20cost%20of%20inaction%20%E2%80%93%20that%20is%2C%20the%20damages%20that%20would%20incur%20if%20we%20do%20not%20invest%20in%20climate%20finance%20%E2%80%93%20would%20be%20a%20whopping%20USD%201%2C266%20trillion.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CThis%20figure%20is%2C%20however%2C%20likely%20to%20be%20a%20dramatic%20underestimate%20of%20the%20true%20cost%20of%20inaction%2C%20since%20it%20does%20not%20capture%20losses%20to%20nature%20and%20biodiversity%2C%20and%20those%20induced%20by%20conflict%20and%20migration%2C%20among%20others.%20Indeed%2C%20the%20cost%20of%20inaction%20only%20promises%20to%20rise%20with%20insufficient%20mitigation%20and%20inadequate%20adaptation%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20report%20noted.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EMore%20reason%20for%20action%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20WMO%E2%80%99s%20report%20is%20important%20because%20it%20will%20inform%20discussions%20at%20the%20climate%20ministerial%20meeting%20that%20is%20being%20held%20in%20Copenhagenon%20March%2021%20and%2022.%20The%20Copenhagen%20Climate%20Ministerial%2C%20as%20it%20is%20called%2C%20is%20the%20first%20political%20high-level%20meeting%20of%20climate%20ministers%20since%20the%20last%20Conference%20of%20Parties%20(the%20world%E2%80%99s%20biggest%20climate%20conference)%20COP28%2C%20which%20was%20held%20in%20Dubai%2C%20UAE%2C%20last%20November.%20At%20the%20ministerial%2C%20climate%20leaders%20and%20ministers%20from%20around%2040%20countries%20will%20discuss%20the%20outcomes%20of%20COP28%20and%20the%20expectations%20from%20the%20upcoming%20COP29%20at%20Baku%2C%20Azerbaijan.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAt%20the%20start%20of%20the%20ministerial%20on%20March%2021%2C%20Intergovernmental%20Panel%20on%20Climate%20Change%20(IPCC)%20Chair%20Jim%20Skea%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ipcc.ch%2F2024%2F03%2F21%2Fipcc-chairs-copenhagen-climate-ministerial%2F%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Esaid%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20that%20the%20scale%20and%20pace%20of%20climate%20change%20pose%20unprecedented%20challenges%20for%20humanity.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CAs%20confirmed%20by%20WMO%2C%202023%20was%20the%20hottest%20year%20on%20record%2C%20with%20particularly%20startling%20extremes%20in%20ocean%20temperatures%E2%80%A6Our%20latest%20report%20showed%20that%20with%20every%20increment%20of%20warming%20the%20world%20will%20become%20more%20and%20more%20dangerous%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.%20%E2%80%9CBeyond%201.5%C2%B0C%20warming%2C%20we%20will%20see%20new%20risks%20will%20emerge%20associated%20with%20sea%20level%20rise%2C%20permafrost%20degradation%2C%20biodiversity%20loss%2C%20water%20scarcity%2C%20more%20extreme%20weather%2C%20food%20insecurity.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAnd%20the%20IPCC%E2%80%99s%20recent%20work%20%E2%80%93%20in%20terms%20of%20energy%20demand%2C%20technology%2C%20and%20more%20%E2%80%93%20%E2%80%9Chas%20shown%20that%20we%20have%20the%20means%20and%20the%20tools%20to%20address%20these%20challenges%2C%20if%20we%20choose%20to%20use%20them%E2%80%9D%2C%20he%20added.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ESkea%20also%20touched%20on%20what%20can%20be%20expected%20from%20the%20IPCC%E2%80%99s%20seventh%20assessment%20cycle%20that%20will%20be%20unveiled%20in%20the%20years%20to%20come.%20In%20early%202027%2C%20the%20IPCC%20should%20release%20a%20Special%20Report%20on%20Cities%20and%20Climate%20Change%3B%20and%20by%20the%20end%20of%202027%2C%20a%20methodology%20report%20on%20carbon%20dioxide%20removal%20technologies%20and%20carbon%20capture%20utilization%20and%20storage%20%E2%80%9Cwhich%20will%20inform%20the%20submission%20of%20national%20inventories%E2%80%9D%2C%20he%20said.%20%E2%80%9CAnd%20during%202028%2C%20the%20Working%20Groups%E2%80%99%20Co-Chairs%20hope%20to%20have%20finalised%20the%20three%20Working%20Group%20Reports.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20WMO%E2%80%99s%20annual%20State%20of%20Climate%20report%20on%20March%2019%20also%20came%20two%20days%20before%20the%20launch%20UNDP%E2%80%99s%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.undp.org%2Flibya%2Fpress-releases%2Fun-development-programme-disrupts-global-television-airwaves-shocking-weather-forecasts-future-mobilize-climate-action-today%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CWeather%20Kids%20campaign%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fwatch%3Fv%3DD5I83ywM-ew%5C%22%3Ewhich%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fwatch%3Fv%3DD5I83ywM-ew%5C%22%3E%C2%A0will%20air%20on%20news%20channels%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20more%20than%2080%20countries.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CIt%E2%80%99s%20not%20just%20a%20weather%20report%20to%20us%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20children%20say%20at%20the%20end.%20%E2%80%9CIt%20is%20our%20future.%E2%80%9D%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1711095307000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2021%2F08%2F17121156%2Fheat-wave.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fenvironment%2F2023-was-hottest-year-on-record-2024-to-get-worse-wmo-report%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22With%20several%20records%20being%20broken%2C%20including%20record%20high%20greenhouse%20gas%20levels%20and%20sea%20surface%20temperatures%2C%20and%20record%20lows%20of%20sea%20ice%20cover%20in%20the%20Antarctic%2C%20the%20UN%20body%20has%20issued%20a%20%E2%80%9CRed%20Alert%E2%80%9D%20to%20the%20world.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fenvironment%2F2023-was-hottest-year-on-record-2024-to-get-worse-wmo-report%22%2C%22cd