r%20of%20democracy%26quot%3B%20and%20an%20%26quot%3Bannouncement%20of%20dictatorship.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMr%20Kejriwal's%20plea%20will%20be%20heard%20by%20a%20special%20bench%20of%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20comprising%20Justices%20Sanjiv%20Khanna%2C%20Bela%20Trivedi%20and%20MM%20Sundresh%20today.%C2%A0The%20Delhi%20Chief%20Minister%20is%20also%20expected%20to%20be%20produced%20before%20a%20special%20Prevention%20of%20Money%20Laundering%20Act%20(PMLA)%20court%20while%20the%20ED%20may%20seek%20a%2010-day%20custody%20for%20further%20interrogation.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESecurity%20around%20the%20ED%20office%20and%20the%20Chief%20Minister's%20residence%20have%20been%20heightened%2C%20with%20the%20Delhi%20Police%20and%20central%20armed%20police%20forces%20setting%20up%20additional%20barricades%20in%20anticipation%20of%20the%20planned%20protests.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20scrapped%20excise%20policy%2C%20introduced%20to%20bring%20an%20overhaul%20to%20the%20national%20capital's%20liquor%20business%2C%20promised%20a%20more%20modern%20shopping%20experience%20with%20discounts%20and%20offers.%20However%2C%20Delhi%20Lieutenant%20Governor%20Vinai%20Kumar%20Saxena's%20order%20to%20investigate%20alleged%20irregularities%20prompted%20the%20policy's%20cancellation.%20The%20AAP%20accuses%20Mr%20Saxena's%20predecessor%2C%20Anil%20Baijal%2C%20of%20making%20last-minute%20changes%20that%20adversely%20affected%20the%20policy's%20revenue%20expectations.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETwo%20prominent%20AAP%20leaders%2C%20Manish%20Sisodia%20and%20Sanjay%20Singh%2C%20are%20already%20under%20judicial%20custody%20in%20connection%20with%20the%20case.%20Mr%20Sisodia%2C%20the%20former%20Delhi%20Deputy%20Chief%20Minister%2C%20was%20arrested%20by%20the%20Central%20Bureau%20of%20Investigation%20(CBI)%20on%20February%2026%20last%20year%2C%20while%20Mr%20Singh%2C%20a%20Rajya%20Sabha%20member%2C%20was%20arrested%20by%20the%20ED%20on%20October%205.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1711085340000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-03%2F01rk8oco_arvind-kejriwal-pti_625x300_22_March_24.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Farvind-kejriwal-spends-night-at-probe-agency-office-after-arrest-5287764%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Delhi%20Chief%20Minister%20Arvind%20Kejriwal%20spent%20the%20night%20at%20the%20Enforcement%20Directorate%20(ED)%20office%20yesterday%20after%20his%20arrest%20in%20connection%20with%20a%20money%20laundering%20case%20linked%20to%20alleged%20irregularities%20in%20the%20scrapped%20Delhi%20excise%20policy%202021-22.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Farvind-kejriwal-spends-night-at-probe-agency-office-after-arrest-5287764%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-ndtv-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Farvind-kejriwal-spends-night-at-probe-agency-office-after-arrest-5287764%2Famp%2F1%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Farvind-kejriwal-spends-night-at-probe-agency-office-after-arrest-5287764%2Famp%2F1%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Matching%20Donors%20to%20Political%20Parties%20Should%20Not%20Have%20Depended%20on%20SBI%20Revealing%20Unique%20Numbers%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F22105735%2Ftowfiqu-barbhuiya-xkArbdUcUeE-unsplash.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20It%20is%20stunning%20that%20the%20Bharatiya%20Janata%20Party%20(BJP)%2C%20which%20came%20up%20with%20the%20dubious%2C%20now-scrapped%20scheme%20and%20held%20office%20for%20six%20years%2C%20despite%20having%20encashed%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fhow-much-money-did-the-bjp-really-get-from-electoral-bonds%5C%22%3Ewhopping%20Rs%208%2C251%20crore%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20electoral%20bonds%2C%20said%20it%20had%20not%20maintained%20%E2%80%9Cparticulars%E2%80%9D%20of%20the%20numerous%20donors%20it%20had.%20Neither%20did%20the%20Trinamool%20Congress%2C%20Congress%2C%20Bharat%20Rashtra%20Samithi%20and%20Biju%20Janata%20Dal%2C%20among%20other%20large%20beneficiaries%20of%20the%20scheme%2C%20put%20the%20donors%20on%20record%20to%20the%20Election%20Commission%20in%20sealed%20covers.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20suspense%20was%20over%20yesterday%20as%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20forced%20the%20State%20Bank%20of%20India%20to%20cough%20up%20the%20unique%20bond%20numbers%2C%20and%20the%20EC%20made%20them%20public.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20why%20did%20it%20take%20for%20citizens%20to%20wait%20for%20the%20SBI%20to%20share%20unique%20bond%20numbers%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20March%2018%2C%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20directed%20the%20SBI%20to%20disclose%20the%20unique%20numbers%20stamped%20on%20the%20electoral%20bonds%2C%20but%20it%20declined%20to%20issue%20any%20instruction%20to%20the%20SBI%20to%20reveal%20data%20prior%20to%20April%2012%2C%202019%20on%20the%20grounds%20that%20it%20would%20amount%20to%20%E2%80%9Creopening%E2%80%9D%20its%20February%2014%20judgment%20(which%20had%20struck%20down%20the%20electoral%20bonds%20scheme).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20would%20it%20have%20meant%20a%20reopening%20of%20the%20order%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20apex%20court%E2%80%99s%20interim%20orders%20passed%20on%20the%20case%20in%202019%20and%20in%202023%20make%20it%20explicit%20that%20details%20should%20have%20been%20made%20available%20to%20the%20Election%20Commission.%20The%20Supreme%20Court%2C%20in%20both%20its%202019%20and%202023%20interim%20orders%2C%20had%20put%20the%20onus%20categorically%20on%20the%20political%20parties%20and%20the%20EC%20to%20account%20for%20the%20money%2C%20amounts%20and%20who%20the%20donors%20were.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ESupreme%20Court%3A%202019%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20April%2017%2C%202019%2C%20Jagdeep%20S.%20Chokkar%20of%20the%20electoral%20reforms%20watchdog%2C%20Association%20of%20Democratic%20Reforms%20(ADR)%2C%20one%20of%20the%20primary%20petitioners%2C%20had%20cited%20four%20paragraphs%20which%20formed%20the%20operative%20part%20of%20the%20SC%E2%80%99s%20April%2012%2C%202019%20order%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fsupreme-court-electoral-bonds-interim-order%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fem%3E.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Col%20start%3D%5C%2211%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3E%3Cem%3E%20All%20that%20we%20would%20like%20to%20state%20for%20the%20present%20is%20that%20the%20rival%20contentions%20give%20rise%20to%20weighty%20issues%20which%20have%20a%20tremendous%20bearing%20on%20the%20sanctity%20of%20the%20electoral%20process%20in%20the%20country.%20Such%20weighty%20issues%20would%20require%20an%20in-depth%20hearing%20which%20cannot%20be%20concluded%20and%20the%20issues%20answered%20within%20the%20limited%20time%20that%20is%20available%20before%20the%20process%20of%20funding%20through%20the%20Electoral%20Bonds%20comes%20to%20a%20closure%2C%20as%20per%20the%20schedule%20noted%20earlier.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3E%3Cem%3E%20The%20Court%2C%20therefore%2C%20has%20to%20ensure%20that%20any%20interim%20arrangement%20that%20may%20be%20made%20would%20not%20tilt%20the%20balance%20in%20favour%20of%20either%20of%20the%20parties%20but%20that%20the%20same%20ensures%20adequate%20safeguards%20against%20the%20competing%20claims%20of%20the%20parties%20which%20are%20yet%20to%20be%20adjudicated.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3E%3Cem%3E%20In%20the%20above%20perspective%2C%20according%20to%20us%2C%20the%20just%20and%20proper%20interim%20direction%20would%20be%20to%20require%20all%20the%20political%20parties%20who%20have%20received%20donations%20through%20Electoral%20Bonds%20to%20submit%20to%20the%20Election%20Commission%20of%20India%20in%20sealed%20cover%2C%20detailed%20particulars%20of%20the%20donors%20as%20against%20the%20(sic)%20each%20Bond%3B%20the%20amount%20of%20each%20such%20bond%20and%20the%20full%20particulars%20of%20the%20credit%20received%20against%20each%20bond%2C%20namely%2C%20the%20particulars%20of%20the%20bank%20account%20to%20which%20the%20amount%20has%20been%20credited%20and%20the%20date%20of%20each%20such%20credit.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3E%3Cem%3E%20The%20above%20details%20will%20be%20furnished%20forthwith%20in%20respect%20of%20Electoral%20Bonds%20received%20by%20a%20political%20party%20till%20date.%20The%20details%20of%20such%20other%20bonds%20that%20may%20be%20received%20by%20such%20a%20political%20party%20up%20to%20the%20date%20fixed%20for%20issuing%20such%20bonds%20as%20per%20the%20Note%20of%20the%20Ministry%20of%20Finance%20dated%2028.2.2019%2C%20i.e.%2015.5.2019%20will%20be%20submitted%20on%20or%20before%2030th%20May%2C%202019.%20The%20sealed%20covers%20will%20remain%20in%20the%20custody%20of%20the%20Election%20Commission%20of%20India%20and%20will%20abide%20by%20such%20orders%20as%20may%20be%20passed%20by%20the%20Court.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fol%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20explains%20why%20some%20parties%2C%20of%20course%20excluding%20the%20BJP%2C%20Congress%2C%20TMC%2C%20BRS%2C%20BJD%20and%20other%20big%20fish%2C%20did%20the%20right%20thing%20by%20naming%20their%20donors%20in%20sealed%20covers%20then%20itself.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fbajaj-finserv-cyrus-poonawalla-top-donors-ncp-2019-polls%5C%22%3ENationalist%20Congress%20Party%20(NCP)%2C%3C%2Fa%3E%20Aam%20Aadmi%20Party%20(AAP)%2C%20Samajwadi%20Party%20(SP)%2C%20Rashtriya%20Janata%20Dal%20(RJD)%2C%20Janata%20Dal%20(United)%2C%20Goa%20Forward%20Party%2C%20Janata%20Dal%20(Secular)%20and%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fsikkim-party-got-bonds-worth-rs-50-lakh-from-gujarat-based-pharma-company%5C%22%3ESikkim%20Democratic%20Party%20(SDF)%3C%2Fa%3E%20did%20furnish%20all%20details%20in%20May%2C%202019%20to%20the%20Election%20Commission.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ESupreme%20Court%3A%202023%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOther%20parties%20like%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fdmk-got-at-least-rs-504-crore-from-future-gaming-group-in-electoral-bonds-ec-data-reveals%5C%22%3EDMK%20and%20the%20AIADMK%3C%2Fa%3E%20furnished%20details%20including%20the%20names%20of%20their%20donors%20to%20the%20Election%20Commission%20after%20the%20Supreme%20Court%E2%80%99s%202023%20interim%20order.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20November%202%2C%202023%2C%20the%20court%20again%20ordered%20the%20EC%20that%20it%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.livelaw.in%2Farticles%2Fpolitical-parties-bound-to-disclose-details-of-electoral-bonds-donors-as-per-supreme-courts-2019-2023-orders-252676%5C%22%3E%E2%80%9Cshall%20produce%20up%20to%20date%20until%20September%2030%2C2023%20in%20terms%20of%20the%20interim%20directions%20which%20were%20issued%20on%20April%2012%2C%202019.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESignificantly%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thehindu.com%2Fdata%2Felectoral-bonds-data-bjp-received-rs-6060-crore-highest-among-all-parties%2Farticle67951830.ece%23%3A~%3Atext%3DBJP%2527s%2520share%2520in%2520the%2520total%2520bonds%2520encashed%2520was%2520over%252047.5%2525%26amp%3Btext%3DThe%2520Bharatiya%2520Janata%2520Party%2520encashed%2Cbonds%2520encashed%2520was%2520over%252047.5%2525.%5C%22%3Ethe%20party%20that%20benefitted%20the%20most%3C%2Fa%3E%20through%20electoral%20bonds%20%E2%80%93%20the%20BJP%20%E2%80%93%20defied%20the%20interim%20order%20while%20responding%20to%20the%20EC%E2%80%99s%20call%20once%20again%2C%20as%20per%20the%20Supreme%20Court%E2%80%99s%202023%20directive.%20The%20BJP%E2%80%99s%20submissions%20made%20on%20November%203%2C%202023%20go%20ahead%20and%20justify%20the%20absence%20of%20those%20crucial%20details%2C%20citing%20scheme%20rules%20and%20of%20it%20being%20anchored%20in%20donor%20anonymity.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20BJP%20had%20written%20to%20the%20EC%20in%20the%20submission%20which%20is%20now%20public%2C%20that%20since%20electoral%20bonds%20were%20introduced%20%E2%80%9Cwith%20the%20aim%20of%20bringing%20only%20accounted%20for%20funds%20in%20political%20funding%20while%20protecting%20the%20donors%20from%20any%20consequences%20therefrom%E2%80%9D%2C%20it%2C%20therefore%2C%20%E2%80%9C%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thehindu.com%2Fnews%2Fnational%2Fbjp-did-not-maintain-names-particulars-of-electoral-bond-donors%2Farticle67961300.ece%5C%22%3Eis%20not%20required%20to%20maintain%20the%20names%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20particulars%20of%20the%20donors%20of%20the%20electoral%20bonds%20and%20as%20such%20the%20party%20has%20not%20maintained%20these%20particulars%E2%80%9D.%20It%20also%20cited%20the%20%E2%80%9Capplicable%20laws%E2%80%9D%20to%20justify%20its%20move.%20The%20%E2%80%9Claw%E2%80%9D%20cited%20is%20of%20course%20now%20decreed%20%E2%80%9Cunconstitutional%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20opening%20of%20the%20sealed%20covers%20by%20the%20EC%20as%20per%20the%20top%20court%E2%80%99s%20March%2018%20order%2C%20revealed%20that%20the%20TMC%2C%20Congress%2C%20Telugu%20Desam%20party%2C%20YSR%20Congress%2C%20Bharat%20Rashtra%20Samithi%2C%20and%20Biju%20Janata%20Dal%20too%20by%20%C2%A0not%20disclosing%20who%20had%20given%20them%20bonds%2C%20ended%20up%20ignoring%20a%20key%20aspect%20of%20the%20Supreme%20Court%E2%80%99s%202019%20interim%20order.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EVital%20time%20was%20lost%20in%20the%20run%20up%20to%20the%20general%20elections%20as%20big%20parties%20did%20not%20furnish%20the%20information%2C%20even%20in%20sealed%20covers%2C%20to%20the%20Election%20Commission.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECitizens%20need%20to%20know%20who%20is%20funding%20parties%20asking%20for%20their%20votes%2C%20to%20be%20able%20to%20make%20sense%20of%20their%20connections%20to%20big%20business%2C%20and%20then%20make%20informed%20choices%20about%20who%20should%20represent%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1711085304000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F22105735%2Ftowfiqu-barbhuiya-xkArbdUcUeE-uns